# Author-facing consolidated migration diff for draft-ietf-intarea-schc-protocol-numbers-02

Source: copied from the most complete available terminology migration diff (Gemini). Consolidated analysis records any source disagreements.

Terminology and architectural-framing migration of
draft-ietf-intarea-schc-protocol-numbers-02 to draft-ietf-schc-architecture-06.

Assumes the three additive edits in schc-architecture-edits.md have been accepted
(Architecture adaptation need: Trivial).

Complete for all technical, architectural, and normative text. Boilerplate, Status
of This Memo, Copyright Notice, Acknowledgments, and Authors' Addresses are omitted
as unaffected. No location in this diff is blocked on an unaccepted Architecture
change; there are no <<BLOCKED>> markers.

Normative language (RFC 2119 / RFC 8174) is preserved unchanged throughout: the
single MUST in Section 4 is neither relaxed nor strengthened, and the SHOULD in
Section 3 is retained verbatim.

Two changes are classified REQUIRED FOR CONCEPTUAL ALIGNMENT in verdicts.md and
therefore do alter what the draft asserts, though not what any implementation does:
the Section 1.2 decomposition of "session (called instance)", and the Section 6.3
statement of RuleID scope. They are marked below.


================================================================================
Abstract
================================================================================

  This document requests an Internet Protocol Number, an Ethertype, and
  UDP port assignment for SCHC.  The Internet Protocol Number request
  is so that SCHC can be used for IP independent SCHC of other
  transports such as UDP and ESP.  The Ethertype is to support generic
  use of native SCHC over any IEEE 802 technology for IP and non-IP
  protocols.  The UDP port request is to support End-to-End SCHC
  through potentially blocking firewalls.

(unchanged: the Abstract makes no architectural claim requiring migration)


