Architectural judgment was exercised at exactly three points, each once:

  1. Section 1.2 -- "session (called instance)" decomposed into Instance and
     Session; recognising that "MAC-Layer endpoints" is a link-layer term and
     must not become -06's Endpoint, while "more powerful endpoint" two
     sentences later must.
  2. Section 3 -- recognising that the source-IP-address table is dispatch
     information reached through a Discriminator, not flat node-local state.
  3. Section 6.3 -- resolving RuleID scope in the Context-scoped direction,
     and recognising that "domains of use" is a false friend of -06's Domain.

Every other change follows from these three decisions without further
